                <p>The scrambler silhouette is rooted in the glorious days of motorcycling, where riders would strip down their road bikes and modify them with higher ground clearance, knobbly tires, and high-mounted exhausts to tackle rough terrain and fire trails. Royal Enfield’s latest iteration, the <span class="font-weight-700">Scrambler 450, </span>takes that authentic, no-nonsense spirit and infuses it with cutting-edge engineering from their new 450cc platform, first seen in the Himalayan 450.</p>
