                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Google-Powered Navigation:</span> The highly popular Royal Enfield Tripper Navigation system, either as standard or an integrated part of the TFT screen, is expected to offer clear, turn-by-turn directions, a massive boon for both touring and exploring new trails.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">All-LED Lighting:</span> Expect an LED headlight, tail lamp, and turn indicators, offering better illumination and a modern premium look.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Other Expected Features: </span>Ride-by-wire technology, which allows for multiple riding modes (such as Road and Off-Road), a USB charging port, and perhaps even a basic level of traction control, could be on the cards to elevate its safety and convenience profile.</li>
